caption: Last week was our first time we went to this restaurant. But It is surely not the last. We enjoyed the evening very much with the good service, with the great  cuisine and booze and with the friendly payment. We will surely go back there in a short time.

Great Thai place, pretty authentic on those funky back flavors. Thats when you know your getting a better meal. The meals have a great umami depth of flavor.  The vegetables were cooked just right, the chicken was also seasoned well and could be enjoyed all on it's own. I had another meal with the Crispy Pork Belly, it was very good as well, perfectly fried and crispy. It's a tiny shop but they are making a great meal.

Suross almost feels too good to be true. Not only is it easily the best tasting Thai in the area, it's by far the most affordable. Staff is always extremely friendly and delivery is lightning fast. Couldn't ask for more.
The food is delicious!

I Never write reviews but that’s just how upset I am. We waited over an hour for our food, and when I called to ask the lady was unapologetic seemed like I was bothering her because they “are busy today”. When the food finally arrived it was just a little warm almost cold and to top it off our Thai teas looked like carrot juices, we asked for 1 without ice and either they gave us all 3 without ice or the ice melted from the time they served it to they time they delivered it. So disappointed it’s always something when we order for delivery, the food is ok but when you’re set a lunch time and don’t get to eat because of bad service or incorrect orders it’s just not worth the frustrations this was our last straw.

The best Thai tea I’ve had in a long time!! The food was also good and the chicken Pad Thai was not dry which seems to be the problem in many places. The reason I only gave it 4 stars was because I did taste a hint of shrimp when it was supposed to be chicken I do love shrimp but I have to be in the mood for it so it was a bit disappointing to taste it when the desired taste was chicken. Otherwise, I would definitely recommend them!

i love this place so much! i got here almost every week. the lunch special is amazing. my favorite dishes are the spicy udon noodles and the cashew nut dish, both with mock duck. so much flavor -- some of the best thai food i've ever had. the service is always kind and quick, and the storefront is lovely, too. such a neighborhood gem!

Really cute, and cozy little Thai place on Broadway. Food is very delicious and staff are polite. They have a little red pay phone which I thought was really cute and I’m pretty sure it actually works but I didn’t try it.
It was too much heavy and sweet, maybe others  like it this way, also my stomach hurts a bit, I hope it’s not because one of the ingredients.
I had see my friends this area and we want Thai foods. I had Teriyaki Salmon and such an unique delicious. Definitely recommended when you feel thai foods in this area

This is some of the best pad thai I’ve ever had. I stopped liking and ordering pad thai for years because every place I got it from it came dry and didn’t have a balanced blend of flavors. I had a random hankering for it and decided to give this place a chance. If you’re looking for a delicious, juicy, flavorful pad thai, look no further. Im so so pleased!!! thank you so much to the chefs at suross thai, your food deeply comforted my soul.
Best Thai place in Washington heights. Got Rama peanut and red curry once. So tasty and unique. I think it’s more healthier than the typical Thai place too
Very good food and timely service
The spot is nice and spacious, the menu was yummy and the prices were very affordable. rapidly, effective service and very personal waiters. I highly recommend this place.

was a regular customer here.. upon the last delivery order, the delivery person very rudely shoved a menu in my face, aggressively pointing out that I am outside of their delivery zone (by 5 blocks) and that I was inconveniencing them for ordering delivery. I understand that that is the case, but I was ordering from them multiple times a week through Seamless which showed that I was in their radius. Perhaps get your Seamless listing sorted out instead of having your employees shouting at regular customers that they are inconveniencing you by literally just providing you business. food is absolutely mediocre and in some cases awful but very cheap.

I have been living in the area for 10 years and had almost given up on yummy Thai cuisine. That is until today. I ordered the Udon lunch special with shrimp and a spring roll for $9.95?! Wasn't expecting a mind-blowing experience but, omg. So delicious. Also tried the pad thai, delicious, and the shrimp dumplings: very plump and delicious. WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN ALL MY LIFE?????? Thank you for a great dining experience. You've earned us as customers.

I meet friends in this lovely place from time to time! This is my favorite restaurant to dine.  I go to this spot regularly. The food is just great, the staff members are helpful and the prices are fair. I like meeting in this spot to have a nice meal.

Love SUROSS Thai! So much that I’ve ordered 2 times this week and many times before that! I usually get the Pad Thai or Green Curry + Spring Rolls. I also love their Thai Tea with milk. Their delivery is super prompt and the food comes packaged well. When I’ve ordered take out, it’s usually available immediately- though if you order for an 11am pickup when they open, it may be a few mins after. I recommend placing the order on their website instead of Seamless etc because it’s better for them AND they give you a slight discount! I really love their lunch specials that start at $8.95 on weekdays and include a full size entree, a small side salad and a veggie spring roll. It’s a killer deal.
Great food, good portions, fair price, kind people, cute shop. I’ll be back!
About a week ago, I had the homemade iced lemonade tea and Thai iced coffee. Very good and reasonably priced except that the lemonade tea was slightly sweeter to my tasting.
Awesome food and awesome service.

I have ordered 3x from this place, and I won't again. The food doesn't truly represent  Thai food. I think that calling it Thai food os an attention grabber- a bait and switch.  This is a step up from Chinese takeout and not in a good way. They are in inconsistent in their food- one day you get Jasmin rice another day regular white rice. Their  garlic chicken was tasteless, and gummy. It didn't even look like chicken. They are stingy in their portions. They serve a few pieces of your choice of protein with lots of veggies.  I'm not impressed, not pleased and won't waste my money.

We did not enjoy some of the food like the tofu because it was extremely greasy and tasteless. Some of the soups, like the coconut soup, were awful, and the chicken stalk was horrible and spoiled. When we ordered the meal, the only thing we were okay with was the rice and vegetables/seafood mix. We strongly do not recommend this restaurant. Instead, we believe a more enjoyable meal would come from a Chinese or Japanese take out place!
I will never ever ever place a order with these ppl...no manners no respect the delivery guy called hang up..I called bck the restaurant they hang up.aswelllll.....customer lost....Columbia hospital
Small and warm place. The food is delicious.
It’s a cute place with amazing food. Not only they have traditional Thai food, but also they have some innovative Thai food. It is definitely worth to try it out here! 😘😘😘
Very lovely place.

Super yummy with super friendly staff. We have been trying to find good crab wontons in the city for what feels like forever. FINALLY found them here!! So delicious aswell as the salmon curry and spicy udon noodles. Will definitely order again!
Y’all gotta try this soup!!! ❤️ #surossnyc #surossthaibistro

I was happy to see a new Thai restaurant while walking last night.  However, NYC Thai food is usually not that good, so I was skeptical, but eager to try it.  For $8-$10,  the lunch special is a very good deal.  From 12pm-4pm, you get a bottle of water, a salad, choice of appetizer, and entree.  So far I have had well over a dozen Spicy Basil dishes here, a Rama dish, a few rice dishes, plus spring rolls and gyoza.  The food here is much better than at Tung Thong 181.  However, as is typical in New York, the dishes sometimes contain a bit too much salt and soy sauce.  If they tone those down, they'll have a much better taste experience.  Otherwise the food is very fresh, and I tend to come back here at least 1x-2x a week (although the cashiers never seem to recognize me, lol).  The place is very small inside and has only a few tables.  The inside also has a faux rustic feel which looks a bit silly (you'll see what I mean).    Still, it's pleasant enough if you can get a seat.   Otherwise I imagine they'll thrive as a take out place.  Now if we can only get a Trader Joe's in Washington Heights!   Then we're set.
Solid pineapple fried dice and amazing curry puffs! Almost always get the puffs when i have extra room.
I love their $8 lunch special, very delicious authentic Thai food. It’s a sweet hole in the wall that is popular in Washington Heights!
This is the best Thai food I’ve found in the Washington Heights. The staff are also quite friendly! I highly recommend the Pad Thai and Massaman.
Very cute, quick service, cosy little place. We had dinner and the shrimp dumplings were great.
Great shrimp pad thai, good place for Thai food in the area
Great service and super tasty Pad Thai!
great service and delicious food! i definitely recommend the pad thai
This spot constantly delivers. They serve excellent dishes for affordable prices, there no long wait even when the place is packed.
Pad Thai was extremely fishy. Basil chicken too spicy. Very disappointed.
Excellent food, The Pineapple fried rice is so spicy delicious!!!!!

Great Little bistro with a very varied menu. Food for all taste and cravings at affordable prices. The establishment is small yet cozy and welcoming. Staff is friendly and helpful. This is definitely a top notch place for Thai food in the heights.

This site is my first choice site.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to visit this restaurant. when  I want to go to a delicious lunchon, this is the place that comes straight to my head. exeptionalgorgeous and many types of  food and a large menu.trained staff, and great mood. Also, the expence is decent. I praise this restaurant with no hesitation.
Would definitely recommend trying this spot. Fantastic character, yummy food, fantastic service. Keep it up.

I ordered the Sriacha Fried Rice and the Spicy Basil Udon Noodles - more vegetables than I'm used too in these dishes but was very good. I like my food very spicy next time I would ask for it spicier, but outside of that error on my part, the place is cozy and very quick service.
Awesome Thai food, best in the heights. I usually don’t write reviews, but the effort of the presentation, the amazing flavors, and the great service had to be talked about. I’ll be back!
First class shrimp dumplings
Really cute small place

Good food

We visited on a weekend for brunch. The inside was surprisingly small, since I was expecting a full-on “restaurant” type eatery. It seems that most businesses they have are either pick up or delivery. They did have a couple of small tables, and a small counter seating by the window.  They have some enticing lunch special menu at great price, and our luck would have it, they offer it for brunch too! They come with complimentary side salad, a choice of starter, and a water. The water can be upgraded to Thai Iced Tea or Soda for additional cost. We got the Thai Iced Tea (additional $2 for upgrade from water). It was really good, kind of nutty, and very sweet as expected.  We had Vegetable Gyoza and Fried Tofu as starters. They were small in portion, but they are starters... Gyoza were steamed, not fried. Tofu were very firm, with a bit of kick to it from the tasty sauce.  For main, we had Massaman Curry with Fried Fillet Fish, and Street Pork Noodle Soup.  Curry was coconut-y and sweet, but not too sweet. Nice amount of rice and loads of lightly fried white fish, which was very tasty! The Noodle Soup was so good! Light with almost translucent broth and noodle, not heavy at all. Earthy and comfy, very homey and flavorful.  It was very satisfying, we were full with just a little over $20! The female staff was very friendly and welcoming also, we will be sure to return!
Uber eats delivery. Appetizers were a little salty and curry was not that great either. Unimpressed. Vegetables in curry were not fresh. Definitely had more flavorful thai food.

Perfectly cooked salmon with my Massuman curry. I like the Thai/Latin fusion touches to acknowledge the culture of the neighborhood. The curry puff empanadas are delicious. Cant wait to try their seafood Thai paella next time. The rustic farm decor is cute.
Unexpectedly good thai food in the middle of the heights. The noodle dishes are good but the curry is really where it's at.  Lots of flavor decent depth and solid portion size.
Amazing food, especially for me since I’m a vegan. You have many options.
Great Thai food in an area that doesn't have too many options for East Asian food. Lunch menu is where you'll stretch your dollar :)

The sweetest servers I've ever seen in fast-food. Since their opening, they have been welcoming even when I was not going to order. The food is clean but it wasn't the flavorful Thai fried rice that I expected.
Ordered multiple times already and each time, the food just seems to get better and better. Incredibly healthy options to choose from.

We had the lunch specials and the food was great! Definitely the best Thai restaurant in the neighborhood. It is clean and cute, and very friendly staff. Highly recommend the Pad Thai and Udon noodle dishes.
Friendly staff,  really cute small restaurant.  Food is delicious 🌶
Fried whole fish.... Always Tamarind soy chile sauce flavor.... Crab rangoon. Just do it
Excellent new Thai restaurant in Washington Heights. Highly recommend.
Great food , great people , great Atmosphere  . Amazing prices and love it ! Nice thai music .
A great place to eat , very healthy and tasty food. The service here is great and they don’t charge you a lot :) I would recommend 100%
Great place! Amazing food and people !!!
Great atmosphere, and the food is amazing; I would recommend for anyone who hasn't visited this place to try the Massaman Curry
I love the decor and the food is plated beautifully and taste great
Welcome to Washington Heights!!! The food is delicious!! The sauces are amazing!! It’s very fresh and the desserts are yummy. Su Ross is a welcome addition to our neighborhood!!!

First time at Suross Thai Bistro today for lunch. The atmosphere is homie and service was great. We ordered the shrimp Pad Thai which was very flavorful and crispy pork with the Suross Fried Rice which was delicious. I will definitely ba back!
Amazing food and service!!!

Great lunch special! The gyoza and garlic chicken were delicious and only $8, with a good portion size. Will definitely be coming back to try other things! There are 2 two-person tables inside and 3 barstools so not a ton of seating, but it wasn't too busy.

My new favorite Thai place in Washington Heights. I ordered a weekend lunch special which was awesome and super fairly priced. Good portion and really great flavors! The restaurant looked very clean and the staff was friendly and helpful.

Great food at great prices. Had the Pad Thai lunch special today and it was served with soup and salad for about $9. (Previously had the Massaman and Green curries, which are also excellent.) Fast and tasty, will definitely be a repeat customer.
Great spot for a quick bite. I ordered the chicken pad thai with veggie spring rolls. Artfully presented and well seasoned, but the chicken was on the dry side.

Note: This used to be Hua Yung Kitchen.  I will definitely miss my Chinese go-to place, but SUROSS is a fantastic addition to the neighborhood. A cozy Thai  spot for take-out or a quick bite.  Prices are comparable to the 181 Tung Thong nearby and other Thai places in the area. Although the sit-down area is not as big, the food is top quality and very tasty! I usually use Pad Thai as a "baseline" comparison in Thai restaurants and here, it is definitely the best I've had in the neighborhood.  The problem others have is either too oily, too sweet, or a combination of both. SUROSS does it just right.  Highly recommend giving them a try, especially now with their 20% discount. I know I will be back!
